			<div class="inner">
				<div class="left">
					<img src="g1.png" width="74" height="74"
					 alt="The Glider (glider 115)" />
				</div>

				<div class="right">
					<p><a href="g1.lif">This pattern</a>
					was discovered by John Conway, 1970.</p>

					<p>It repeats every 4 generations,
					translated diagonally one cell,
					for a total speed of c/4.
					Every 2 generations, the same pattern appears,
					flipped diagonally.</p>

					<p>The same evolutionary sequence works in 256 rules ranging from
					<a href="../b3s23/">B3/S23</a>
					to <a href="../b3678s0235678/">B3678/S0235678</a>.</p>
				</div>

